The aristocrats of Downton Abbey will have a royalty in their midst as an extra who is related to the Queen joins the cast.

Flora Ogilvy, who is 45th in line to the throne, will have a part in the new series which will be aired in September.

She is as an extra in the ITV show and filmed alongside Dame Maggie Smith, 78 and Hugh Bonneville, 49, reported the Daily Express.

